    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      93.38,
      478.11,
      445.18,
      492.15
    ],
    "text": "threshold issue in reviewing a judgment of an original court.",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      522.39,
      540.28,
      536.43
    ],
    "text": "The facts relating to this matter are straight forward in that, the Accused-",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      544.59,
      543.6,
      558.63
    ],
    "text": "Appellant was charged before the magistrate\u2019s court under Sections 64 (a) of the",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      566.79,
      498.25,
      580.83
    ],
    "text": "Sri Lanka Bureau of Foreign Employment Act No.21 of 1985, as amended.",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      588.87,
      543.49,
      602.91
    ],
    "text": "The basis of the charge was that, the Accused-Appellant demanded and received",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      611.1,
      543.31,
      625.14
    ],
    "text": "a sum of Rs.450, 000 from one Illeperumage Dilhani Pradeepa for the purpose of",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      633.3,
      543.34,
      647.34
    ],
    "text": "securing her employment in Cyprus. I do not wish to delve into the facts of the",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      655.5,
      543.59,
      669.54
    ],
    "text": "case as they would be of no relevance in deciding the questions of law referred",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      677.58,
      543.52,
      691.62
    ],
    "text": "to. Suffice it to state that, at the conclusion of the trial, the learned Magistrate, by",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      731.38,
      542.6,
      755.86
    ],
    "text": "5",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      73.04,
      543.5,
      87.08
    ],
    "text": "his judgment dated 19th March, 2013 found the Accused-Appellant guilty and",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.0,
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      95.26,
      399.7,
      109.3
    ],
    "text": "proceeded to convict the Accused-Appellant as charged.",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      139.54,
      543.5,
      153.58
    ],
    "text": "Aggrieved by the judgment aforesaid, the Accused-Appellant challenged the",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      161.74,
      543.54,
      175.78
    ],
    "text": "conviction by lodging an appeal in the High Court. When the matter was taken",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      183.94,
      540.16,
      197.98
    ],
    "text": "up before the High Court, an objection was raised on behalf of the Attorney-",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      206.02,
      465.94,
      220.06
    ],
    "text": "General, the 2nd Respondent-Respondent to the present application.",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      250.45,
      543.49,
      264.49
    ],
    "text": "The learned State Counsel contended that the Accused-Appellant has no right of",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      272.65,
      543.58,
      286.69
    ],
    "text": "appeal against a conviction in terms of the provisions of the Sri Lanka Bureau of",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      294.73,
      515.05,
      308.77
    ],
    "text": "Foreign Employment Act No.21 of 1985 (hereinafter referred to as the Act).",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      339.13,
      543.19,
      353.17
    ],
    "text": "The basis of the objection appears to be, that the right of appeal is a substantive",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      361.33,
      543.3,
      375.37
    ],
    "text": "right and not a matter of procedure. The learned judge of the High Court having",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      383.41,
      543.26,
      397.45
    ],
    "text": "upheld the objection raised on behalf of the state, dismissed the appeal without",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      405.61,
      270.8,
      419.65
    ],
    "text": "considering the merits of the case.",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      450.03,
      500.17,
      464.07
    ],
    "text": "The present appeal is from the said order of the learned High Court Judge.",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      472.11,
      543.59,
      486.15
    ],
    "text": "At the hearing of the appeal the learned counsel for the Accused-Appellant",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      494.31,
      543.64,
      508.35
    ],
    "text": "referred to Section 31 of the Judicature Act as well as to the Article154 (P) (3) (a)",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      516.51,
      543.61,
      530.55
    ],
    "text": "of the Constitution. Both these are, provisions conferring appellate powers on the",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      538.71,
      543.39,
      552.75
    ],
    "text": "Court of Appeal and the High Court. While these provisions confer appellate",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      560.79,
      547.09,
      574.83
    ],
    "text": "powers, in Martin Vs Wijewardene 1989 2 S.L R 409 His Lordship Justice Jameel",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      582.99,
      543.62,
      597.03
    ],
    "text": "rejected the argument that these provisions impliedly confer substantive right of",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      605.22,
      116.81,
      619.26
    ],
    "text": "appeal.",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      649.5,
      543.41,
      663.54
    ],
    "text": "The learned counsel for the Accused-Appellant also relied on Section 317 of the",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      671.7,
      543.54,
      685.74
    ],
    "text": "Code of Criminal Procedure Act No.15 of 1979. The State, based their argument",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      693.89,
      543.54,
      707.93
    ],
    "text": "on the principle that the right of appeal is neither a fundamental nor an inherent",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      731.38,
      542.6,
      755.86
    ],
    "text": "6",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      73.04,
      540.16,
      87.08
    ],
    "text": "right, but a creation of a statute. It was contended on behalf of the Attorney-",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      95.26,
      543.22,
      109.3
    ],
    "text": "General that there can be no inherent right of appeal from any judgment for",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      117.34,
      499.09,
      131.38
    ],
    "text": "determination unless an appeal is expressly provided for, by the law itself.",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      161.74,
      543.38,
      175.78
    ],
    "text": "The issue at hand, however, can be resolved by application of the provisions of",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      183.94,
      543.61,
      197.98
    ],
    "text": "the International Covenant on Civil and Political Right Act No.56 of 2007",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      206.02,
      315.32,
      220.06
    ],
    "text": "(hereinafter referred to as the ICCPR Act).",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      250.45,
      543.26,
      264.49
    ],
    "text": "Sri Lanka is a state party to the International Covenant on Civil and Political",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      272.65,
      543.62,
      286.69
    ],
    "text": "Rights (ICCPR) where an inherent right of appeal is recognized against any",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      294.73,
      543.51,
      308.77
    ],
    "text": "conviction. The Covenant, which was adopted by the General Assembly of the",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      316.93,
      543.61,
      330.97
    ],
    "text": "United Nations on 16th of December, 1966, entered into force on 23rd March,",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.0,
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      339.13,
      476.5,
      353.17
    ],
    "text": "1976. Sri Lanka acceded to the aforesaid covenant in the year 1980.",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      383.41,
      543.58,
      397.45
    ],
    "text": "Sri Lanka being a dualist state, implementation of the ICCPR requires that it be",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      405.61,
      543.22,
      419.65
    ],
    "text": "incorporated into domestic law which was accomplished in 2007 with the",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      427.83,
      543.55,
      441.87
    ],
    "text": "passage of ICCPR Act. The goal of the covenant is to define international human",
