      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      450.03,
      543.28,
      464.07
    ],
    "text": "rights standards and to require signatory states to adopt measures to enforce",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      472.11,
      543.26,
      486.15
    ],
    "text": "those rights. The rights provided by the ICCPR are regarded as the basic human",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      494.31,
      543.6,
      508.35
    ],
    "text": "rights that should be viewed as restrictions (against derogation) on the",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      516.51,
      543.43,
      530.55
    ],
    "text": "governments of signatory states. The ICCPR is valid for its signatory states and",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      538.71,
      448.3,
      552.75
    ],
    "text": "every signatory government is obligated to observe its provisions.",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      582.99,
      543.6,
      597.03
    ],
    "text": "Paragraph 5 of Article 14 of the Covenant lays down that \u201cEveryone convicted of",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      605.22,
      543.6,
      619.26
    ],
    "text": "a crime shall have the right of his conviction and sentence being reviewed by a",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      627.42,
      269.84,
      641.46
    ],
    "text": "higher tribunal according to law.",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      671.7,
      543.61,
      685.74
    ],
    "text": "Jixi Zhang in his article Fair Trial Rights in ICCPR (Journal of Politics and Law -",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      693.89,
      546.65,
      707.93
    ],
    "text": "Vol 2 No.4 2009) states that \u201cArticle 14, paragraph 5 provides that everyone",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      731.38,
      542.6,
      755.86
    ],
    "text": "7",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      73.04,
      546.65,
      87.08
    ],
    "text": "convicted of a crime shall have the right to have their conviction and sentence",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      95.26,
      546.47,
      109.3
    ],
    "text": "reviewed by a higher tribunal according to law. The right to appeal is also",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      117.34,
      546.6,
      131.38
    ],
    "text": "known as the right to be reviewed. The Human Rights Committee considers that",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      139.54,
      546.49,
      153.58
    ],
    "text": "the right to appeal is absolute. The absolute nature of the right to appeal is",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      161.74,
      546.43,
      175.78
    ],
    "text": "reflected in the following three aspects: the right to appeal applies to all types of",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      183.94,
      407.97,
      197.98
    ],
    "text": "crimes, that is, not only applies to serious crimes\u2026\u2026\u2026 \u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      228.22,
      460.42,
      242.26
    ],
    "text": "The preamble to the Covenant exemplifies the objectives and states:",
    "fonts": [
      "FootlightMTLight"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      271.62,
      500.37,
      294.28
    ],
    "text": "\u201cConsidering that in accordance with the principles",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      305.46,
      500.62,
      328.12
    ],
    "text": "proclaimed in the Charter of the United Nations, recognition",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      339.42,
      500.3,
      362.08
    ],
    "text": "of the inherent dignity and of the equal and inalienable",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      373.26,
      500.54,
      395.92
    ],
    "text": "rights of all members of the human family is the foundation",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      407.22,
      370.15,
      429.88
    ],
    "text": "of freedom, justice and peace in the world\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      440.96,
      500.37,
      463.62
    ],
    "text": "Recognizing that these rights derive from the inherent dignity",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      463.64,
      237.89,
      486.3
    ],
    "text": "of the human person,",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      493.64,
      500.37,
      516.3
    ],
    "text": "Recognizing that, in accordance with the Universal",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      516.32,
      500.56,
      538.98
    ],
    "text": "Declaration of Human Rights, the ideal of free human beings",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      538.88,
      500.31,
      561.54
    ],
    "text": "enjoying civil and political freedom and freedom from fear",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      561.44,
      500.4,
      584.1
    ],
    "text": "and want can only be achieved if conditions are created",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      584.12,
      500.38,
      606.78
    ],
    "text": "whereby everyone may enjoy his civil and political rights, as",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      606.83,
      406.75,
      629.49
    ],
    "text": "well as his economic, social and cultural rights,",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      636.83,
      500.43,
      659.49
    ],
    "text": "Considering the obligation of States under the Charter of the",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      659.39,
      500.38,
      682.05
    ],
    "text": "United Nations to promote universal respect for, and",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      100.34,
      682.07,
      399.19,
      704.73
    ],
    "text": "observance of, human rights and freedoms,\u2026\u2026",
    "fonts": [
      "VinerHandITC"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 7,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      731.38,
      542.6,
      755.86
    ],
    "text": "8",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 7,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      117.34,
      543.36,
      131.38
    ],
    "text": "The ICCPR Act was enacted in the discharge of Sri Lanka\u2019s obligation as a",
